      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gutzon Borglum, Creator of Mount Rushmore</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maggie Thoms letter comments on December 5 article on Gutzon Borglum, creator of Mount Rushmore (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was delighted with your article on Gutzon Borglum (Art: A Monument Maker on a Smaller Scale, Dec. 5) and hope to see the exhibition at the Stamford Museum and Nature Center. If I am not mistaken, didn't he design one of the overpasses on the Merritt Parkway?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was delighted with your article on Gutzon Borglum (Art: A Monument Maker on a Smaller Scale, Dec. 5) and hope to see the exhibition at the Stamford Museum and Nature Center. If I am not mistaken, didn't he design one of the overpasses on the Merritt Parkway?</p>
        <p>You're right -- most people do not know the artist of Mount Rushmore and I am wondering how many Americans know the sculptor of the Statue of Liberty? (Frederic Auguste Bartholdi).</p>
        <p>MAGGIE THOMS  Stony Creek</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
